    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ea4c55ffd8dc7155",
      "text": "We had better unwind. Experience in education led to interest in experiential learning which led to living in a forest which led to embodied math which led to Spencer Brown which led to a Ph.D. about symbolic thinking which led to our group at Interval, protected from the vagaries of underfunded institutions, trying to improve the foundations of computational mathematics. One result might be unexpected: our culture’s time-honored and universally accepted place-value number system is not the only way to count, it is not necessarily the best way to do arithmetic, it is not even well designed."
    },
